01:29:15.340 --> 01:29:17.000
And one of the
things that I thought

01:29:17.000 --> 01:29:18.620
that you were
bringing up a lot was

01:29:18.620 --> 01:29:22.400
that notion of the guilt that--

01:29:22.400 --> 01:29:24.845
was it you that was
talking about the guilt?

01:29:24.845 --> 01:29:25.970
Michelle spoke [INAUDIBLE].

01:29:25.970 --> 01:29:26.595
Yeah, Michelle.

01:29:26.595 --> 01:29:28.490
OK, and I wanted to
connect it to this.

01:29:28.490 --> 01:29:32.540
So this notion of the built
where Patrick is constantly

01:29:32.540 --> 01:29:34.730
feeling that, and in
a way, constrained

01:29:34.730 --> 01:29:38.640
within a certain kind
of effective economy

01:29:38.640 --> 01:29:40.550
that has been
already constructed

01:29:40.550 --> 01:29:42.900
for particular people
more than others.

01:29:42.900 --> 01:29:46.970
So I wanted to conjunct this too
because Michelle was bringing

01:29:46.970 --> 01:29:51.560
yup the white sensibility, what
it means to be a middle class

01:29:51.560 --> 01:29:53.250
person working with people.

01:29:53.250 --> 01:29:55.550
But that is bringing
from the vantage point

01:29:55.550 --> 01:29:59.060
of being black, and recognizing
that the majority are

01:29:59.060 --> 01:30:00.930
black and Latino people.

01:30:00.930 --> 01:30:03.770
So maybe speak a little
bit to that tension.

01:30:03.770 --> 01:30:07.760
And how do you rapture these
dominant, effective economies

01:30:07.760 --> 01:30:12.995
that really log in particular
populations more than others.

01:30:17.410 --> 01:30:20.020
Does one of you
want to start there?

01:30:20.020 --> 01:30:22.750
Sure.

01:30:22.750 --> 01:30:27.260
So the question is more about
the tensions between perhaps

01:30:27.260 --> 01:30:31.190
mine speaking for more of
an outsider standpoint and--

01:30:31.190 --> 01:30:32.164
[INAUDIBLE]

01:30:37.034 --> 01:30:44.095
But Eddie was putting himself
in in a very different way

01:30:44.095 --> 01:30:46.662
that you were, the positionality
and [INAUDIBLE] structure.

01:30:46.662 --> 01:30:49.775
So speaking to that
a little bit more,

01:30:49.775 --> 01:30:53.880
because I think it speaks to the
tensions in terms of writing,

01:30:53.880 --> 01:30:55.740
since we talk
about writing here,

01:30:55.740 --> 01:30:58.845
but also in terms of how
do you really rapture

01:30:58.845 --> 01:31:01.118
this dominant
[INAUDIBLE] economies

01:31:01.118 --> 01:31:03.740
from different positionalities.

01:31:03.740 --> 01:31:06.890
Yeah, it's really hard.

01:31:06.890 --> 01:31:10.670
When I went to
Arkansas, look, anybody

01:31:10.670 --> 01:31:13.160
know how many
Asian-Americans or Asians are

01:31:13.160 --> 01:31:15.450
in Phillips County, Arkansas?

01:31:15.450 --> 01:31:17.215
One, me.

01:31:17.215 --> 01:31:20.570
OK, no there were the Chinese
guys who own the restaurant.

01:31:20.570 --> 01:31:21.440
I would go say hi.

01:31:21.440 --> 01:31:22.398
But they're from China.

01:31:22.398 --> 01:31:24.530
My parents are from Taiwan.

01:31:24.530 --> 01:31:26.314
So I was definitely an outsider.

01:31:26.314 --> 01:31:27.230
There was no question.

01:31:27.230 --> 01:31:28.150
People would stare.

01:31:28.150 --> 01:31:29.540
I was very conspicuous.

01:31:29.540 --> 01:31:32.170
My kids, to get under my
nerves, would be like,

01:31:32.170 --> 01:31:33.680
are you related to Jackie Chan?

01:31:33.680 --> 01:31:38.120
And I'd be like, no,
I'm actually not.

01:31:38.120 --> 01:31:40.620
Being a [INAUDIBLE] was really--

01:31:40.620 --> 01:31:41.870
it's fine.

01:31:41.870 --> 01:31:44.290
I don't take whatever
microaggressions.

01:31:44.290 --> 01:31:45.610
I don't care.

01:31:45.610 --> 01:31:48.640
In a rural area, I'm the one
who has the resources to leave.

01:31:48.640 --> 01:31:51.280
Immigrants don't go to
rural areas to get jobs.

01:31:51.280 --> 01:31:54.170
So I didn't take it
personally at all.

01:31:54.170 --> 01:31:56.842
So I was definitely
outsider, but sometimes I

01:31:56.842 --> 01:31:59.300
get upset when people were
like, why don't you just go back

01:31:59.300 --> 01:31:59.900
to where you're from?

01:31:59.900 --> 01:32:00.650
Where am I from?

01:32:00.650 --> 01:32:02.480
I'm from a place where I was
also an outsider in Kalamazoo,

01:32:02.480 --> 01:32:03.230
Michigan.

01:32:03.230 --> 01:32:07.610
And my parents never taught me
anything about townies history

01:32:07.610 --> 01:32:09.874
because they grew up in
an authoritarian regime

01:32:09.874 --> 01:32:12.040
where they couldn't learn
about their own histories.

01:32:12.040 --> 01:32:14.150
Taiwan has been colonized
for four centuries.

01:32:14.150 --> 01:32:20.270
So it's confusing
because I'm constantly

01:32:20.270 --> 01:32:22.670
aware of that power dynamic.

01:32:22.670 --> 01:32:25.280
I would rather there be
African-American educators

01:32:25.280 --> 01:32:26.730
in schools and in prisons.

01:32:26.730 --> 01:32:28.310
But I wouldn't force
them to do that.

01:32:28.310 --> 01:32:29.990
They should go do
whatever they want to do.

01:32:29.990 --> 01:32:30.865
You know what I want?

01:32:30.865 --> 01:32:34.160
More Asian-Americans
to participate,

01:32:34.160 --> 01:32:36.620
to feel solidarity,
to put themselves

01:32:36.620 --> 01:32:39.620
at risk, to own the pain,
because, like you said,

01:32:39.620 --> 01:32:41.390
we're all part of this complex.

01:32:41.390 --> 01:32:45.350
So it was hard for me to
write because I understood.

01:32:45.350 --> 01:32:47.020
I tried to understand
positionality.

01:32:47.020 --> 01:32:48.400
I wanted to be honest about it.

01:32:48.400 --> 01:32:50.540
I didn't hide from it.

01:32:50.540 --> 01:32:52.860
I had a Post-it
note on my computer

01:32:52.860 --> 01:32:55.490
that said stop
hiding, because I was

01:32:55.490 --> 01:33:00.050
hiding beneath the outrage of
this history that is grotesque.

01:33:00.050 --> 01:33:04.400
But you have to put
yourself on the page.

01:33:04.400 --> 01:33:06.290
You have to put the
inequality on the page

01:33:06.290 --> 01:33:07.961
and work through it.

01:33:07.961 --> 01:33:08.460
The one--

01:33:08.460 --> 01:33:08.740
Yeah.

01:33:08.740 --> 01:33:08.990
I'm sorry.

01:33:08.990 --> 01:33:09.490
Go for it.

01:33:09.490 --> 01:33:10.610
Yeah.

01:33:10.610 --> 01:33:13.760
So positionality is something
I think about a lot.

01:33:13.760 --> 01:33:17.270
I think the biggest credit,
the reason I've been most--

01:33:17.270 --> 01:33:21.190
I think the reason I've been
successful in the classroom

01:33:21.190 --> 01:33:25.960
with these specific students
is because I believe very, very

01:33:25.960 --> 01:33:28.540
firmly that it is not
only enough to reflect

01:33:28.540 --> 01:33:31.714
the physical likeness of the
students, or in other words,

01:33:31.714 --> 01:33:33.880
just because a black person
walks into the classroom

01:33:33.880 --> 01:33:38.200
doesn't mean by virtue of that
you're going to learn from me.

01:33:38.200 --> 01:33:40.810
But it means so much more
to reflect the likeness

01:33:40.810 --> 01:33:42.615
of their character, right?

01:33:42.615 --> 01:33:44.740
Because when they have
someone in the classroom who

01:33:44.740 --> 01:33:48.340
has tattoos, who gestures the
way they gesture, who speaks

01:33:48.340 --> 01:33:50.260
the same language
that they speak,

01:33:50.260 --> 01:33:53.710
it becomes the meeting
place between aspiration

01:33:53.710 --> 01:33:56.510
and what's practical, Or
in other words, they think,

01:33:56.510 --> 01:33:58.990
oh, Eddie's doing this,
and Eddie's like me.

01:33:58.990 --> 01:34:00.850
So maybe that means I can do it.

01:34:00.850 --> 01:34:01.750
You get it?

01:34:01.750 --> 01:34:04.449
And so that's the
biggest credit.

01:34:04.449 --> 01:34:06.490
The problem is not everybody
could pull that off.

01:34:06.490 --> 01:34:07.030
But--

01:34:07.030 --> 01:34:10.320
[LAUGHING]

01:34:10.320 --> 01:34:11.287
[INAUDIBLE]

01:34:14.710 --> 01:34:20.901
This may be a good moment
to end our discussion.

